description:
In \`sign_sync\` (line 87), \`.join().unwrap_or_else(|_| ...)\` silently discards the panic payload with \`|_|\`. A reader unfamiliar with \`thread::JoinHandle::join\` returning \`Result<T, Box<dyn Any + Send>>\` will not know why the payload is dropped rather than logged or re-panicked. The reason is that \`Box<dyn Any + Send>\` cannot be reliably downcasted to a message without additional convention — but this is non-obvious.

Add a brief inline comment:

```rust
.join()
.unwrap_or_else(|_| {
    // panic payload is Box<dyn Any + Send>; not reliably downcasted, so discard it
    Err(SecretError::Backend {
```

One line removes a re-read.
